			<div n="notes" xml:lang="en">
				<note place="foot" anchored="false" target="#I.19" type="editorial" id_text="I.19.n">
					<foreign xml:lang="la" rend="italics">urbem</foreign>: An apparent non sequitur, or is it?  Has the power of Rome itself become divine?
				</note>
				<note place="foot" anchored="false" target="#I.26" type="editorial" id_text="I.26.n">
					<foreign xml:lang="la" rend="italics">causa videndi</foreign>: "reason to see".  An unusual construction.  Usually we see gerundive + causa.
				</note>
				<note place="foot" anchored="false" target="#I.34" type="editorial" id_text="I.34.n">
					<foreign xml:lang="la" rend="italics">premeretur</foreign>: the technical term for cheese-making.
				</note>
